modules.description: Provides arithmetic addition and comparison operations for values of type t. Works with specific audio format identifiers such as flac, mikmod, and mp3. Used to represent and compare supported audio codecs in a media processing context.

Handles audio codec comparisons and arithmetic operations, supporting formats like FLAC, MOD, and MP3. It defines type t for codec representation and includes operations to evaluate and contrast audio format capabilities. Users can determine codec compatibility or priority within a media processing pipeline. Examples include checking if a format is supported or calculating codec priority based on defined criteria.

Provides functions for loading and playing audio files, managing music and channel states, and adjusting volume levels. Works with data types such as audio files, music objects, and audio channels. Used to integrate sound effects and background music into multimedia applications built with Tsdl.

Manages audio codec evaluation and comparison, offering type t for format representation and operations to assess capabilities. It supports arithmetic and compatibility checks across formats such as FLAC, MOD, and MP3. Users can determine format support status or compute priority rankings. For example, it can identify if MP3 is compatible with a given system or rank codecs by decoding efficiency.
